$interpreted: Healy: Whew...still a while before we reach the Desert Kingdom...
Jerome: Give up, Healy. Surrender yourself to King Theodore, and his Majesty might consider sparing your family.
Healy: Bastard, if not for you and that madwoman, I would not have ended up in this spot!
Healy: Tsk...almost killed you by accident. I need to keep you alive as a hostage in case that madwoman pursues us!
Jerome: Hmph, save that consideration for yourself.
Jerome: General must've have rushed back to Kingdom of the Sun already and reported your treason to King Theodore!
Healy: You little...are you asking for me to kill you?
Jerome: My life is worth nothing compared to the mission. General Lucien will definitely...
Fredrica: Whew...finally caught up with you guys...give handsome back to me!
Jerome: General!? Why are you here?
Fredrica: What are you talking about? I'm here to rescue you, of course!
Jerome: Then did you send someone back to Kingdom of the Sun to report to King Theodore about Healy's Treason?
Jerome: So...the insignia of the Desert Kingdom's archpriest...
Fredrica: Oh that? I have it right here with me~
Jerome: What...you're throwing yourself to the wolves! You just gave Healy the prime opportunity to get off scot-free!
Fredrica: Well, I was too busy thinking about rescuing you that I just forgot to consider other things~
Healy: Hmph, then as long as I kill both of you, no one will know...
Fredrica: Kill me? You? My my, boy, aren't you full of yourself!
Healy: D-Don't do anything stupid! Your officer is still in our hands...

Fredrica: If you dare even leave a scratch on my dear officer, 
I will personally make sure that you die the most painful death ever imaginable!
Healy: You witch...don't be afraid. Everybody, get her!
Ned: General Fredrica, we're here to help you!
Lisa: So you're the ones who framed Ned! It's payback time!
Healy: D-Damnit. S-Stay away from me, or else I'll kill him...
Fredrica: Whew~ It's finally over~
Jerome: General, your actions are far too reckless!
Fredrica: Aww, come on~ In the end, you're safe as well. Nothing went wrong! Isn't that what we all want?
Jerome: My life is trivial when compared to the kingdom! From the moment I enlisted in the army, I was prepared to give my life for the kingdom's sake!

Fredrica: I will not allow you to say something like that! 
You lose everything when you die!
Fredrica: Besides, you're my most precious...
Jerome: ...General?
Fredrica: ...My most precious subordinate~
Fredrica: You're helpful, have a fun personality and most importantly, you haven't resigned after experiencing all my shenanigans.
Fredrica: You're probably the first officer to do that in five years~
Fredrica: After we get back to the kingdom, we're certainly going to face a lot of dull work. Of course I'm going to need you by my side~
Jerome: So that's what you meant...
Fredrica: Looking forward to working together with you afterward, handsome~
Jerome: General, you're late, AGAIN!
Fredrica: Sorry~ Once I applied those skin care products on my face, I had to wait until my skin has completely absorbed all the essence~
Fredrica: I won't do it next time. Can you forgive me? Please~
Jerome: ...Forget it. We accidentally prevented Healy's act of treason anyway. That should more or less atone for our misconducts in King Theodore's eyes.
Fredrica: Ooh, I like your way of thinking. Then let's begin our trip back to the kingdom!
Fredrica: Handsome, is something wrong?
Jerome: Nothing, I just remembered that time when we first met here. General seemed to be really drunk and was mumbling something about a cheater?
Jerome: Did something happen back then?
Fredrica: Hoho, are you having an interest in my past relationships already?
Fredrica: You gotta do better than that, handsome~A man like you is too good to be with someone like me~
Jerome: General, you're joking around with me again...
Fredrica: This time...it's not a joke~
Jerome: General, please wait for me!
